    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Hey! I am working on this. I am thinking of something simple as the following:\r\n\r\n```\r\ncontract CancellablePullPayment is PullPayment {\r\n\r\n  function cancelPayment(address _payee) internal {\r\n    uint256 payment = payments[_payee];\r\n\r\n    require(payment != 0);\r\n\r\n    payments[_payee] = 0;\r\n    totalPayments = totalPayments.sub(payment);\r\n  }\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nWe can make it more complex in case we want to:\r\n\r\n- Be able to cancel partial amounts of money.\r\n- Be able to cancel partial payments. For example if a payment of 100 was set for an address and then a payment of 200 was set for the same address, we could allow cancellations of one or both of those payments.\r\n\r\nI am not sure if those scenarios are useful. What are your thoughts? @maraoz ",
